      <h2 class='text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300'>Types of Scholarships</h2>
      <ul class='mt-4 space-y-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300'>
        <li>
          <strong>Merit-Based Scholarships:</strong> Awarded based on academic performance, achievements,
          or talents.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Need-Based Scholarships:</strong> Given to students who demonstrate financial need,
          often requiring documentation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Subject-Specific Scholarships:</strong> Focused on students pursuing specific fields
          of study (e.g., STEM, arts, humanities).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Country-Specific Scholarships:</strong> Offered to students from specific countries
          or regions to promote diversity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>University-Specific Scholarships:</strong> Provided by universities to attract talented
          students to their programs.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class='mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300'>
        Applying for Scholarships
      </h2>
      <p class='mt-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300'>
        To maximize your chances of securing scholarships, consider the following tips:
      </p>
      <ul class='mt-4 space-y-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300'>
        <li>
          <strong>Start Early:</strong> Research scholarship opportunities well in advance to ensure
          you meet deadlines.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tailor Your Application:</strong> Customize your application to align with the scholarship's
          values and objectives.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Gather Strong References:</strong> Secure recommendation letters from teachers, mentors,
          or employers who can attest to your qualifications.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Write a Compelling Essay:</strong> Clearly express your goals, achievements, and why
          you deserve the scholarship in your application essay.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class='mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300'>
        Financial Aid Options
